Provides: snapcastmpris
Description: MPRIS2 bridge for the local Snapcast client
 snapclientmpris exposes the local Snapcast client (snapclient) on D-Bus
 as an MPRIS2 MediaPlayer2 player. It surfaces the currently playing
 track (title, artist, album, art) from snapserver and lets MPRIS2-aware
 clients pause and resume audio. The daemon runs entirely on asyncio:
 python-snapcast for the snapserver JSON-RPC channel and dbus-fast for
 the MPRIS interface.
 .
 The audio player itself is the snapclient package's snapclient.service;
 this daemon does not spawn snapclient. The shipped systemd units pull
 snapclient.service in via Wants= and order After=.
 .
 By default the bridge registers on the session bus (per-user
 deployment); a legacy system-bus mode is available via the dbus-bus
 key for hifiberry-style installs. The configuration is read from
 $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/snapclientmpris/snapclientmpris.conf with a fallback
 to /etc/snapclientmpris.conf. An example configuration is shipped at
 /usr/share/snapclientmpris/snapclientmpris.conf.
 .
 Both a user systemd unit (default, session bus) and a system unit
 (runs as _snapclient on the system bus, with a matching D-Bus policy
 shipped at /usr/share/dbus-1/) are shipped; neither is auto-enabled.
